00:00:07:130000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:00:07:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:07:130000.Dialogue: I'd be more interested in a scene depicting Spock's conception.

00:00:11:200000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:00:11:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:00:11:200000.Dialogue: Oh, please. For Vulcans, mating... or if you will, PonFahr...

00:00:17:120000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:00:17:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:17:120000.Dialogue: Still, I'd like to know the details. His mother was human. His father is Vulcan. They couldn't just conceive.

00:00:23:040000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:00:23:040000.Speaker: Howard
00:00:23:040000.Dialogue: Maybe they had to go to a clinic. Can you imagine Spock's Dad in a little room with a copy of Pointy Ears and Shapely Rears.

00:00:32:060000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:00:32:060000.Speaker: Raj
00:00:32:060000.Dialogue: How come on Star Trek everybody's private parts are the same? No alien lady ever told Captain Kirk, Hey, get your thing out of my nose.

00:00:42:120000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:00:42:120000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:42:120000.Dialogue: Hi. Can you help me? I was writing an e-mail and the A key got stuck. Now it's just going Aaa...

00:00:49:020000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:00:49:020000.Speaker: Leonard

00:00:55:040000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:00:55:040000.Speaker: Penny
00:00:55:040000.Dialogue: And yogurt. And a little nail polish.

00:00:58:100000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:00:58:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:00:58:100000.Dialogue: I'll take a look at it.

00:01:00:080000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:00:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:00:080000.Dialogue: Gentlemen, switching to local nerd news... Fishman, Chen, Chaudury and McNair aren't fielding a team in the university Physics Bowl this year.

00:01:08:080000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:08:080000.Speaker: Leonard

00:01:09:200000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:09:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:01:09:200000.Dialogue: They formed a barbershop quartet and got a gig playing Knott's Berry Farm.

00:01:15:190000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:15:190000.Speaker: Penny
00:01:15:190000.Dialogue: So, in your world, you're like the cool guys.

00:01:20:170000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:20:170000.Speaker: Howard

00:01:24:030000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:24:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:24:030000.Dialogue: This is our year. With those guys out, the entire Physics Bowl will kneel before Zod.

00:01:29:050000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:29:050000.Speaker: Penny

00:01:30:060000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:30:060000.Speaker: Howard

00:01:32:010000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:32:010000.Speaker: Raj

00:01:36:170000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:36:170000.Speaker: Howard

00:01:39:080000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:39:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:39:080000.Dialogue: You want me to use my intelligence in a tawdry competition? Would you ask Picasso to play Pictionary?

00:01:46:110000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:46:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:46:110000.Dialogue: Would you ask Noah Webster to play Boggle?

00:01:49:210000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:49:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:49:210000.Dialogue: Would you ask Jacques Cousteau to play Go Fish?

00:01:54:010000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:54:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:01:54:010000.Dialogue: Come on, you need a four-person team. We're four people.

00:01:57:040000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:01:57:040000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:01:57:040000.Dialogue: By that reasoning we should also play Bridge, hold up a chuppah and enter the Olympic bobsled competition.

00:02:03:160000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:02:03:160000.Speaker: Penny

00:02:06:080000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:02:06:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:02:06:080000.Dialogue: Sheldon, what, do I need to quote Spock's dying words to you?

00:02:10:080000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:02:10:080000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:02:12:100000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:02:12:100000.Speaker: Leonard

00:02:14:050000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:02:14:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:14:050000.Dialogue: ... outweigh the needs of the few.

00:02:16:090000.Scene: The apartment. Howard is looking at his mobile phone.
00:02:16:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:02:16:090000.Dialogue: Or the one. Damn it, I'll do it.

00:02:45:210000.Speaker: Raj
00:02:45:210000.Dialogue: First order of Physics Bowl business. We need a truly kick-ass team name. Suggestions?

00:02:52:050000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:52:050000.Dialogue: How about the Perpetual Motion Squad?

00:02:55:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:02:55:200000.Dialogue: It's beyond the laws of physics, plus a little heads-up for the ladies.

00:03:01:110000.Speaker: Howard
00:03:01:110000.Dialogue: Perpetual Motion Squad... we can go all night.

00:03:12:140000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:12:140000.Dialogue: Then we could be the Bengal tigers.

00:03:21:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:03:21:020000.Dialogue: Maybe so, but you can't incinerate a Bengal tiger with a magnifying glass.

00:03:28:210000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:28:210000.Dialogue: Let's put it to a vote. All those in favor...

00:03:30:230000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:03:30:230000.Dialogue: Point of order. I move that any vote on team names must be unanimous. No man should be forced to emblazon his chest with a Bengal tiger when common sense dictates it should be an army ant.

00:03:41:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:41:040000.Dialogue: Will the gentleman from the great State of Denial yield for a question?

00:03:46:060000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:46:060000.Dialogue: After we go through the exercise of an annoying series of votes, all of which the gentleman will lose, does he then intend to threaten to quit if he does not get his way?

00:03:54:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:03:54:080000.Dialogue: I move we are the Army Ants. All those in favor?

00:03:58:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:03:58:200000.Dialogue: Good afternoon, and welcome to today's Physics Bowl practice round. I'm Penny, and I'll be your host because apparently I didn't have anything else to do on a Saturday afternoon, and isn't that just a little sad?

00:04:14:180000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:14:180000.Dialogue: It's none of my business, but isn't a guy who can't speak in front of women gonna hold you back a little?

00:04:19:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:19:150000.Dialogue: He'll be okay once the women are mixed into the crowd. He only has a problem when they're one-on-one and smell nice.

00:04:28:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:04:28:160000.Dialogue: I was actually the one who noticed. Okay, let's just start.

00:04:32:050000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:32:050000.Dialogue: Okay, the first question is on the topic of optics. What is the shortest light pulse ever produced? Dr. Cooper.

00:04:38:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:38:070000.Dialogue: And of course, the answer is 130 attoseconds.

00:04:44:160000.Speaker: Penny
00:04:44:160000.Dialogue: Good for you, sweetie. Okay, next question: What is the quantum mechanical effect used to encode data on hard-disk drives?

00:04:53:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:53:110000.Dialogue: And of course the answer is giant magnetoresistance.

00:04:58:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:04:58:090000.Dialogue: And I answered. It's called teamwork.

00:05:02:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:02:130000.Dialogue: Don't you think I should answer the engineering questions? I am an engineer.

00:05:06:150000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:06:150000.Dialogue: By that logic I should answer all the anthropology questions because I'm a mammal.

00:05:16:110000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:16:110000.Dialogue: What artificial satellite has seen glimpses of Einstein's predicted frame dragging?

00:05:21:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:21:190000.Dialogue: And of course, it's Gravity Probe B.

00:05:24:140000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:24:140000.Dialogue: Sheldon, you have to let somebody else answer.

00:05:30:050000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:30:050000.Dialogue: What do manners have to do with it? This is war.

00:05:34:120000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:34:120000.Dialogue: Were the Romans polite when they salted the ground of Carthage to make sure nothing would ever grow again?

00:05:40:030000.Speaker: Penny
00:05:40:030000.Dialogue: Leonard, you said I only had to ask questions.

00:05:44:210000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:44:210000.Dialogue: The objective of the competion is to give correct answers. If I know them, why shouldn't I give them?

00:05:49:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:05:49:150000.Dialogue: Some of us might have the correct answers, too.

00:05:52:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:05:52:090000.Dialogue: Oh, please. You don't even have a PhD.

00:05:59:020000.Speaker: Leonard
00:05:59:020000.Dialogue: Maybe we should take a little break.

00:06:09:210000.Speaker: Howard
00:06:09:210000.Dialogue: He compared Sheldon to a disposable feminine cleansing product one might use on a summer's eve.

00:06:19:070000.Speaker: Penny
00:06:19:070000.Dialogue: Yeah, and the bag it came in.

00:06:25:160000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:06:25:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:25:160000.Dialogue: Leonard, excellent. I want to show you something.

00:06:28:050000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:06:28:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:28:050000.Dialogue: Can it wait? I need to talk to you.

00:06:30:010000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:06:30:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:30:010000.Dialogue: Just look. I've designed the perfect uniforms for our team. The colors are based on Star Trek: The Original Series. The three of you will wear Support Red, and I will wear Command Gold.

00:06:41:100000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:06:41:100000.Speaker: Leonard

00:06:43:120000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:06:43:120000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:06:45:230000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:06:45:230000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:45:230000.Dialogue: Isn't that confusing? AA might mean something else to certain people.

00:06:50:170000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:06:50:170000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:06:50:170000.Dialogue: Why would a Physics Bowl team be called Anodized Aluminum?

00:06:55:010000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:06:55:010000.Speaker: Leonard

00:06:59:100000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:06:59:100000.Speaker: Leonard
00:06:59:100000.Dialogue: Check it out, I got you a Batman cookie jar.

00:07:04:090000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:04:090000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:07:07:080000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:07:080000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:07:080000.Dialogue: Well, you're a friend, and you like Batman and cookies, and you're off the team.

00:07:15:190000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:15:190000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:07:17:040000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:17:040000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:17:040000.Dialogue: Howard, Raj and I just had a team meeting.

00:07:19:130000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:19:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:19:130000.Dialogue: Yes, we did. I just came from there

00:07:22:030000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:22:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:22:030000.Dialogue: Okay, I don't know where you just came from, but it could'nt have been a team meeting because I wasn't there. Ergo, the team did not meet.

00:07:30:050000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:30:050000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:30:050000.Dialogue: Okay, let me try it this way: I was at a coffee klatch with a couple of friends, and one thing led to another, and it turns out you're off the team.

00:07:40:130000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:40:130000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:07:41:130000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:41:130000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:41:130000.Dialogue: Because you're taking all the fun out of it.

00:07:44:010000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:44:010000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:44:010000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, is the winner of the Physics Bowl the team that has the most fun?

00:07:48:000000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:48:000000.Speaker: Leonard
00:07:48:000000.Dialogue: Okay, let me try it this way: You're annoying and no one wants to play with you anymore.

00:07:55:080000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:07:55:080000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:07:55:080000.Dialogue: I see. At this point I should inform you that I intend to form my own team and destroy the molecular bonds that bind your very matter together and reduce the resulting particulate chaos to tears.

00:08:12:210000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:08:12:210000.Speaker: Leonard

00:08:15:070000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:08:15:070000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:08:18:010000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:08:18:010000.Speaker: Leonard

00:08:19:150000.Scene: The same, later. Sheldon is on his laptop. Leonard enters.
00:08:19:150000.Speaker: Sheldon

00:08:28:160000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:28:160000.Dialogue: So who'd he get to be on his team?

00:08:36:100000.Speaker: Raj
00:08:36:100000.Dialogue: He's using psychological warfare. We must reply in kind. I say we wait until he looks at us, then laugh like, Yes, you are a smart and strong competitor, but we are also smart and strong, and we have a reasonable chance of defeating you.

00:08:52:120000.Speaker: Leonard
00:08:52:120000.Dialogue: How exactly would that laugh go?

00:08:59:130000.Speaker: Howard
00:08:59:130000.Dialogue: That sounds more like, We are a tall, thin woman who wants to make a coat out of your Dalmatians.

00:09:07:160000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:07:160000.Dialogue: Let's remember that Sheldon is still our friend and my roommate.

00:09:25:080000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:25:080000.Dialogue: We're going to need a strong fourth for our team.

00:09:28:020000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:28:020000.Dialogue: You know who is apparently very smart is the girl who played TV's Blossom.

00:09:33:130000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:33:130000.Dialogue: She got a PhD. in neuroscience or something.

00:09:35:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:09:35:180000.Dialogue: Raj, we're not getting TV's Blossom to join our Physics Bowl team.

00:09:41:180000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:41:180000.Dialogue: How about the girl from The Wonder Years?

00:09:45:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:09:45:150000.Dialogue: Gentlemen, I believe I've found the solution to all our problems.

00:09:53:160000.Speaker: Raj
00:09:53:160000.Dialogue: Why? Because you slept together, and when she was done with you she discarded you like last night's chutney?

00:10:05:020000.Speaker: Howard
00:10:05:020000.Dialogue: Sometimes you've got to take one for the team.

00:10:10:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:10:170000.Dialogue: Fine. Here I go, taking one for the team... in the sack.

00:10:22:180000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:22:180000.Dialogue: So, Leslie, I have a question for you, and it might be a little awkward, you know, given that I...

00:10:34:050000.Speaker: Leslie
00:10:34:050000.Dialogue: Leonard, there's no reason to feel uncomfortable just because we've seen each other's faces and naked bodies contorted in the sweet agony of coitus.

00:10:43:030000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:43:030000.Dialogue: There's not? Gee, 'cause it sure sounds like there should be.

00:10:47:170000.Speaker: Leslie
00:10:47:170000.Dialogue: Rest assured that any aspects of our sexual relationship regarding your preferences, your idiosyncrasies, your performance are still protected by the inherent confidentiality of the bedroom.

00:10:56:220000.Speaker: Leonard
00:10:56:220000.Dialogue: That's all very comforting, but if it's okay, I'd like to get on to my question now.

00:11:02:170000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:02:170000.Dialogue: We are entering the Physics Bowl, and we need a fourth for our team.

00:11:06:070000.Speaker: Leslie
00:11:06:070000.Dialogue: No, thanks. I'm really busy with my like-sign dilepton supersymmetry search.

00:11:15:190000.Speaker: Howard
00:11:15:190000.Dialogue: Well, we tried. We'll just have to face Sheldonmano y mano y mano a mano.

00:11:22:000000.Speaker: Leslie
00:11:22:000000.Dialogue: Wait, you're going up against Sheldon Cooper? That arrogant, misogynistic, East Texas doorknob that told me I should abandon my work with high-energy particles for laundry and childbearing?

00:11:40:130000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:40:130000.Dialogue: So, how do you feel? Nice and loose? Come to play? Got your game face on? Are you ready?

00:11:49:010000.Speaker: Leonard
00:11:49:010000.Dialogue: Yeah. You know, you don't have to stay for the whole thing.

00:11:51:200000.Speaker: Penny
00:11:51:200000.Dialogue: Oh, no. I want to. Sounds really interesting.

00:12:18:160000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:18:160000.Dialogue: Actually, I don't need a team. I could easily defeat you single-handedly, but the rules require four. So, may I introduce the third-floor janitor, the lady from the lunch room, and my Spanish is not good... either her son or her butcher.

00:12:33:090000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:33:090000.Dialogue: And what about your team? What rat have you recruited to the S.S. Sinking Ship?

00:12:44:040000.Speaker: Leslie
00:12:44:040000.Dialogue: Yeah, Leslie Winkle. The answer to the question, Who made Sheldon Cooper cry like a little girl?

00:12:51:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:12:51:030000.Dialogue: Well, I'm polymerized tree sap, and you're an inorganic adhesive. So whatever verbal projectile you launch in my direction is reflected off of me, returns on its original trajectory and adheres to you.

00:13:05:070000.Speaker: Dr Gablehouser
00:13:05:070000.Dialogue: Okay, if everyone could please take your seats.

00:13:20:210000.Speaker: Leslie
00:13:20:210000.Dialogue: PMS? It's a couple days early...

00:13:26:070000.Speaker: Leonard
00:13:26:070000.Dialogue: It stands for Perpetual Motion Squad.

00:13:29:110000.Speaker: Leslie
00:13:29:110000.Dialogue: Of course. What was I thinking?

00:13:33:020000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:13:33:020000.Dialogue: Good afternoon, everyone, and welcome to this year's Physics Bowl!

00:13:39:160000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:13:39:160000.Dialogue: Today's preliminary match features two great teams. AA versus... PMS.

00:13:55:060000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:13:55:060000.Dialogue: Okay, well, let's jump right in. First question for ten points: What is the iso-spin singlet partner of the pi-zero meson? PMS?

00:14:12:060000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:12:060000.Dialogue: The Velcro on my wrist brace caught on my shirt.

00:14:15:080000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:14:15:080000.Dialogue: Denied. All right, for ten points, What is the lightest element on Earth with no stable isotope?

00:14:24:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:24:000000.Dialogue: And of course, the answer is technetium.

00:14:26:020000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:14:26:020000.Dialogue: Terrific. Next question: What is the force between two uncharged plates due to quantum vacuum fluctuations? PMS?

00:14:35:170000.Speaker: Raj
00:14:35:170000.Dialogue: Sheldon can suck on... the Casimir effect.

00:14:38:070000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:14:38:070000.Dialogue: Correct. How does a quantum computer factor large numbers? PMS?

00:14:55:110000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:14:55:110000.Dialogue: 4.1855 times ten to the seventh ergs per calorie.

00:15:01:030000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:15:01:030000.Dialogue: Lambda equals one over pi r squared n.

00:15:03:170000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:03:170000.Dialogue: 760 degrees Celsius... the approximate temperature of the young lady in the front row.

00:15:09:160000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:15:09:160000.Dialogue: Mr. Wolowitz, this is your second warning.

00:15:14:220000.Speaker: Leslie
00:15:14:220000.Dialogue: Yes, assuming the hypothetical planet has a mass greater than the Earth.

00:15:24:170000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:15:24:170000.Dialogue: Ladies and gentlemen, I hold in my hand the final question. The score now stands. AA: 1,150, PMS: 1,175. So, for 100 points and the match, please turn your attention to the formula on the screens. Solve the equation.

00:15:52:150000.Speaker: Howard
00:15:52:150000.Dialogue: Looks like something they found on the ship at Roswell.

00:15:58:140000.Speaker: Leslie
00:15:58:140000.Dialogue: It's not gonna work if you rush me. You have to let me get there.

00:16:01:150000.Speaker: Leonard
00:16:01:150000.Dialogue: You are never gonna let that go, are you?

00:16:27:140000.Speaker: Gablehouser
00:16:27:140000.Dialogue: I'm sorry, that's incorrect. AA, if you can answer correctly, the match is yours.

00:16:36:200000.Speaker: Howard
00:16:36:200000.Dialogue: He doesn't have it. He's got squat.

00:16:53:020000.Speaker: Third Floor Janitor
00:16:53:020000.Dialogue: The answer is minus eight pi alpha.

00:16:56:000000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:16:56:000000.Dialogue: Hang on a second. That's not our answer. What are you doing?

00:17:03:190000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:03:190000.Dialogue: How do you know anything about physics?

00:17:05:210000.Speaker: Third Floor Janitor
00:17:05:210000.Dialogue: Here I am janitor. In former Soviet Union, I am physicist.

00:17:17:200000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:17:200000.Dialogue: That's a delightful little story, but our arrangement was that you sit here and not say anything... I answer the questions.

00:17:25:070000.Speaker: Sheldon
00:17:25:070000.Dialogue: Look, now, maybe you have democracy now in your beloved Russia, but on this Physics Bowl team, I rule with an iron fist.

00:17:33:050000.Speaker: Gablehouser
